554
00:58:08,080 --> 00:58:11,320
I like that that touches also on this 
idea of, again, maximizing potential,  

555
00:58:11,320 --> 00:58:14,280
the potential of the teams, 
the potential of the employees

556
00:58:14,280 --> 00:58:19,640
Because of course, the really important decisions, 
we don't talk about. This is the most important  

557
00:58:19,640 --> 00:58:26,200
thing. Shopify probably makes... What?... millions 
of decisions every day, like, write this code this  

558
00:58:26,200 --> 00:58:32,000
way, yes, I'm going to add this unit test, maybe 
I'm skipping a unit test. Might be the difference  

559
00:58:32,000 --> 00:58:39,080
between a future production audit. Millions and 
millions of these tiny decisions. So, you're  

560
00:58:39,080 --> 00:58:46,840
not hiring engineers primarily or accountants, 
you're hiring people who make excellent decisions,  

561
00:58:46,840 --> 00:58:53,880
given their specialization and areas they're 
overseeing. And given that, decision making as  

562
00:58:53,880 --> 00:59:05,400
a concept is actually really understudied, I find.
I think these are instances where we can just  

563
00:59:05,400 --> 00:59:11,080
